   - For hexadecimal (base-16), remainders 0-9 map to `0-9` and 10-15 map to `A-F`.
   - For base-36, remainders 0-9 map to `0-9` and 10-35 map to `A-Z`.
   - The remainders are collected in reverse order (least significant digit first), so the resulting string must be reversed to get the correct representation.

